-- Exercises the FIRST-disjointness demotion for ABNF-generated
-- `#[longest]` groups. Every alternative of `op` starts with a
-- distinct byte, so ordered choice matches exactly the same strings
-- as longest-match — the lowering-time wrapper is stripped at compile
-- time and the per-byte dispatch is a plain `/` chain.
--
-- Usage:
--   echo -n "+-*=<>!&|^" | pars examples/abnf-disjoint-alts.pars

@abnf"""
op = "+" / "-" / "*" / "=" / "<" / ">" / "!" / "&" / "|" / "^"
"""

entry = op+;
